In [2]:
import pandas as pd
import os

def load_across_users(base_path, filename):
    dfs = []
    
    # loop through all user folders
    for entry in os.listdir(base_path):
        user_dir = os.path.join(base_path, entry)
        if not os.path.isdir(user_dir):
            # skip non-folders
            continue  

        file_path = os.path.join(user_dir, filename)
        
        if not os.path.exists(file_path):
            # print(f"Skipping: {file_path} (not found)")
            continue
        
        temp = pd.read_csv(file_path)
        temp["user"] = entry
        dfs.append(temp)

    if not dfs:
        raise ValueError(f"No files named {filename} found under {base_path}")
    
    return pd.concat(dfs, ignore_index=True)

df_u1 = df_sleep[df_sleep["user"]== "user_1"].copy()

# Identify numeric and non-numeric columns
numeric_cols = df_u1.select_dtypes(include=['int64', 'float64']).columns
non_numeric_cols = df_u1.select_dtypes(exclude=['int64', 'float64']).columns

# Create aggregation rules
agg_dict = {col: 'sum' for col in numeric_cols}          # merge numeric columns
agg_dict.update({col: 'first' for col in non_numeric_cols})  # keep first value for non-numeric

# Merge user_1s two rows
df_u1_merged = df_u1.groupby('user', as_index=False).agg(agg_dict)

# Replace old user_1 records with the merged one
df_sleep_clean = pd.concat([
    df_sleep[df_sleep['user'] != 'user_1'],  # keep all other users
    df_u1_merged                             # add merged user_1 row
], ignore_index=True)

#categorize period 
def assign_period(hour): 
    if 9 <= hour < 18:
        return "day"
    elif 18 <= hour <= 23:
        return "evening"
df_actigraph_clean["period"] = df_actigraph_clean["hour"].apply(assign_period)
In [23]:
#aggregate activity by period per user
activity_period = df_actigraph_clean.groupby(["user", "period"]).agg(
    mean_activity=("Vector Magnitude", "mean"),
    max_activity=("Vector Magnitude", "max"),
    activity_variability=("Vector Magnitude", "std"),
    mean_heartrate = ("HR", "mean"),
    total_steps=("Steps", "sum")
).reset_index()

#convert day & evening into separate columns 
activity_period_combine = activity_period.pivot(
    index = "user",
    columns = "period",
    values = "mean_activity"
).reset_index()

import numpy as np
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

plt.figure(figsize=(12,6))

width = 0.35
users = activity_period_combine_sleep["user"].astype(str).values
day_vals = activity_period_combine_sleep["day"]
evening_vals = activity_period_combine_sleep["evening"]
tst_vals = activity_period_combine_sleep["Total Sleep Time (TST)"]

x = np.arange(len(users))

# Create main axis
fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(12,6))

# Grouped bar chart
ax.bar(x - width/2, day_vals, width, label="Day", color="skyblue")
ax.bar(x + width/2, evening_vals, width, label="Evening", color="orange")

# Secondary axis for line plot
ax2 = ax.twinx()
ax2.plot(x, tst_vals, color="#2CCE61", linewidth=2, marker="o", label="Total Sleep Time")
ax2.set_ylabel("Total Sleep Time", color="green")
ax2.set_ylim(0, 650)
ax2.grid(False)

# Labels, ticks, title
ax.set_xticks(x)
ax.set_xticklabels(users, rotation=90)

ax.set_xlabel("User")
ax.set_ylabel("Mean Activity (Vector Magnitude)")
ax.set_title("Day vs Evening Activity per User with Total Sleep Time")

# Legends
ax.legend(loc="upper left")
ax2.legend(loc="upper right")

plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()

Sleep analysis¶

In [37]:
import matplotlib.ticker as mticker

def sleep_condition_categorize(x) -> pd.Series:
    #define the bins (cut points)
    bins = [0, 360, 480, float('inf')] #3 sleeping ranges
    
    #define corresponding labels: 
    labels = ['Inadequate', 'Adequate', 'Oversleep']
    return pd.cut(x, bins = bins, labels = labels, right = True).to_numpy()

#apply mapping 
df_sleep_clean['SleepCondition'] = sleep_condition_categorize(df_sleep_clean['Total Sleep Time (TST)'])
                                                     
#plot sleep condition distribution
fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10,8))
plot_args = {"multiple": "stack", "alpha": 0.4, "bins": 40, "binwidth": 20, "binrange": (80, 620)}
sns.histplot(ax=ax, data=df_sleep_clean, x="Total Sleep Time (TST)", hue="SleepCondition", **plot_args)
ax.axvline(x=360, color='#b7c6df', linestyle='--')
ax.axvline(x=480, color='#f1c6d9', linestyle='--')
ax.text(360, 5, "6 hours")
ax.text(480, 5, "8 hours")
ax.set_title("Sleep condition distribution", fontsize=24, pad=20)
ax.set_xlabel("Minutes")

ax.yaxis.set_major_locator(mticker.MultipleLocator(1))

ax.set_xticks(range(80, 620, 40))
ax.grid(False)
plt.show()
